    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>In the circuit shown, the n : 1 step-down transformer and the diodes are ideal. The diodes have no voltage drop in forward biased condition. If the input voltage (in Volts) is $V_s(t) = 10 \\sin\\omega t$ and the average value of load voltage $V_L(t)$ (in Volts) is $\\frac{2.5}{\\pi}$, the value of n is _____.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lxkyfe8e/6ae058ed-ac43-4d59-8c0c-1b0ec57abc18/10f8f7d0-2dbf-11ef-bfc8-2b32b9c46aa5/file-jaoe38c1lxkyfe8f.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lxkyfe8e/6ae058ed-ac43-4d59-8c0c-1b0ec57abc18/10f8f7d0-2dbf-11ef-bfc8-2b32b9c46aa5/file-jaoe38c1lxkyfe8f.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2024 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 4 English\">",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "<p>4</p>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "<p>8</p>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "<p>12</p>"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "<p>16</p>"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given :</p>\n<p>(i) Single phase full wave mid-point Diode Rectifier with $R$-Load.</p>\n<p>(ii) Input voltage $V_s(t)=10 \\sin \\omega t$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mfeabl7m/557550f6-4183-453a-9dd8-15a2f125e876/fcf3b730-8e6f-11f0-af8a-fb4a25e5b24b/file-jaoe38c1mfeabl7n.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mfeabl7m/557550f6-4183-453a-9dd8-15a2f125e876/fcf3b730-8e6f-11f0-af8a-fb4a25e5b24b/file-jaoe38c1mfeabl7n.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2024 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 4 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Transformation ratio</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; (k)=\\frac{V_2}{V_1}=\\frac{N_2}{N_1}=\\frac{1}{n} \\\\ &amp; V_2=\\frac{V_1}{n}=\\frac{V_S}{n} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Case 1: During positive Half cycle.</p>\n<p>$D_1 \\rightarrow \\mathrm{ON}$ and $D_2 \\rightarrow \\mathrm{OFF}$</p>\n<p>$$ V_L=\\frac{V_S}{2 n}\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\, \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(i)$$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp;\\text { Case } 2 \\text { : During Negative Half cycle. }\\\\ &amp;\\begin{aligned} &amp; D_1 \\rightarrow \\mathrm{OFF} \\text { and } D_2 \\rightarrow \\mathrm{ON} \\\\ &amp; V_L=\\frac{-V_S}{2 n} \\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,\\,...(ii)\\end{aligned} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>The DC Output Voltage or Average Output Voltage can be calculated as follows.</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; V_0=V_{d c}=\\frac{1}{\\pi} \\int_0^\\pi\\left(\\frac{V_s}{2 n}\\right) d \\omega t \\\\ &amp; V_0=\\frac{1}{\\pi} \\int_0^\\pi \\frac{V_m}{2 n} \\sin \\omega t d \\omega t \\\\ &amp; V_0=\\frac{V_m}{2 \\pi n} \\int_0^\\pi \\sin \\omega t d \\omega t \\\\ &amp; V_{0(\\mathrm{avg})}=\\frac{V_m}{2 \\pi n}[-\\cos \\omega t]_0^\\pi \\\\ &amp; V_{0(\\mathrm{avg})}=\\frac{V_m}{2 \\pi n}[-\\cos (\\pi)+\\cos (0)] \\\\ &amp; V_{0(\\mathrm{avg})}=\\frac{V_m}{2 \\pi n}[1+1]=\\frac{2 V_m}{2 \\pi n}=\\frac{V_m}{\\pi n} \\\\ &amp; V_{0(\\mathrm{avg})}=\\frac{2.5}{\\pi}=\\frac{V_m}{\\pi n} \\\\ &amp; n=\\frac{V_m}{2.5}=\\frac{10}{2.5}=4 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence the correct option is (A).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2024,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2024",
    "difficulty": null
  },
