    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbezk5am/a0209bae-4ab5-4814-9fb2-5b28fa2f9c7d/d1a6cee0-3fa1-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezk5an.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbezk5am/a0209bae-4ab5-4814-9fb2-5b28fa2f9c7d/d1a6cee0-3fa1-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezk5an.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 2 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Given, $V_{\\text {in }}$ is steep of $-M$ to $+M$</p>\n<p>For $V_0$ versus $V_{\\text {IN }}$ :</p>\n<p>Let $\\quad V_{\\text {IN }}=+M$</p>\n<p>In the bridge rectifier, $D_1$ and $D_3$ are forward bias, and $D_2$ and $D_4$ are reverse bias,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbezl66d/79a279e0-3c0e-409a-b7ff-358aa6d2e2bc/ee248260-3fa1-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezl66e.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbezl66d/79a279e0-3c0e-409a-b7ff-358aa6d2e2bc/ee248260-3fa1-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezl66e.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 2 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\therefore \\quad V_{\\text {in }}-V_0=0 \\Rightarrow V_{\\text {in }}=V_0 $$</p>\n<p>$\\therefore$ For $V_{\\text {in }}=+M \\Rightarrow V_0=M$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} -V_{\\text {in }}+I_{\\text {in }} R &amp; =0 \\\\ I_{\\text {in }} &amp; =\\frac{V_{\\text {in }}}{R}=\\frac{M}{R} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Let $V_{\\text {IN }}=-M$</p>\n<p>$D_1$ and $D_3$ are reverse bias,</p>\n<p>$D_2$ and $D_4$ are forward bias.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbezmen9/a2f5626e-0b9c-4c97-a9b6-598de819a3c5/107e4d50-3fa2-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezmena.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbezmen9/a2f5626e-0b9c-4c97-a9b6-598de819a3c5/107e4d50-3fa2-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbezmena.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 2 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\therefore \\quad \\begin{aligned} V_{\\text {in }}+V_0 &amp; =0 \\\\ V_o &amp; =-V_{\\text {in }}=-[-M]=M \\\\ -V_{\\text {in }}+I_{\\text {in }} \\times R &amp; =0 \\\\ I_{\\text {in }} &amp; =\\frac{V_{\\text {in }}}{R}=\\frac{-M}{R} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbezneli/5350af7d-71a7-4269-9a8a-f1de344c93ec/2c43d460-3fa2-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbeznelj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbezneli/5350af7d-71a7-4269-9a8a-f1de344c93ec/2c43d460-3fa2-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbeznelj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 2 English Explanation 4\"></p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>The diode in the circuit shown below is ideal. The input voltage (in Volts) is given by $V_1=10 \\sin 100 \\pi t$, where time $t$ is in seconds.</p>\n<p>The time duration (in ms, rounded off to two decimal places) for which the diode is forward biased during one period of the input is ________.</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf02j0w/fcb8fa75-329e-4301-b7fa-93a42e81601a/d0d27d00-3fa3-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbf02j0x.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf02j0w/fcb8fa75-329e-4301-b7fa-93a42e81601a/d0d27d00-3fa3-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbf02j0x.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 3 English\">",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "13.32TO13.34",
    "explanation": "<p>Given,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} 2 \\pi f t &amp; =100 \\pi t \\\\ f &amp; =50 \\mathrm{~Hz} \\\\ T_0 &amp; =\\frac{1}{f}=20 \\mathrm{msec} \\\\ V_i &amp; =10 \\sin (100 \\pi t)=10 \\sin \\alpha \\\\ \\alpha &amp; =100 \\pi t \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Diode conducts if $V_i&gt;-5 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p>Diode is OFF if $V_i&lt;-5 \\mathrm{~V}$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mbf03lot/b14c17f4-8c03-4216-ab7f-b1e362e5c5c4/eeb083d0-3fa3-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbf03lou.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mbf03lot/b14c17f4-8c03-4216-ab7f-b1e362e5c5c4/eeb083d0-3fa3-11f0-a491-e768f614f5b9/file-jaoe38c1mbf03lou.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2025 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 3 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$ 10 \\sin \\alpha=-5 $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp;\\begin{aligned} \\alpha &amp; =\\sin ^{-1}\\left(\\frac{-5}{10}\\right) \\\\ \\alpha &amp; =\\frac{7 \\pi}{6}, \\frac{11 \\pi}{6} \\\\ 100 \\pi t_1 &amp; =\\frac{7 \\pi}{6} \\\\ t_1 &amp; =11.66 \\mathrm{msec} \\\\ \\alpha_2 &amp; =100 \\pi t_2=\\frac{11 \\pi}{6} \\\\ t_2 &amp; =18.33 \\mathrm{msec} \\end{aligned}\\\\ &amp;\\text { Diode is OFF from } t_1 \\text { to } t_2\\\\ &amp;\\begin{aligned} t_{\\mathrm{OFF}} &amp; =t_2-t_1=6.66 \\mathrm{msec} \\\\ t_{\\mathrm{ON}} &amp; =T_0-t_{\\mathrm{OFF}}=13.33 \\mathrm{msec} \\end{aligned} \\end{aligned} $$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2025,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2025",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>In the circuit shown below, D$$_1$$ and D$$_2$$ are silicon diodes with cut-in voltage of 0.7 V. $$\\mathrm{V_{IN}}$$ and $$\\mathrm{V_{OUT}}$$ are input and output voltages in volts. The transfer characteristic is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lywnnk9z/99199b6d-8954-4b5b-a142-78fc08f99aca/8eddc770-47fa-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnnka0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lywnnk9z/99199b6d-8954-4b5b-a142-78fc08f99aca/8eddc770-47fa-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnnka0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 5 English\"></p>",
