    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Given circuit is as shown below,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lywnnk9z/99199b6d-8954-4b5b-a142-78fc08f99aca/8eddc770-47fa-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnnka0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lywnnk9z/99199b6d-8954-4b5b-a142-78fc08f99aca/8eddc770-47fa-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnnka0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 5 English Explanation 1\">\n\n<p><b>Case 1 :</b> When $V_{I N}&lt;0.3 \\mathrm{~V}, D_1$ is OFF and $D_2$ is ON . So, the circuit becomes,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lywntlz2/f41a6f62-d741-430f-a76b-38c103998297/370829e0-47fb-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywntlz3.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lywntlz2/f41a6f62-d741-430f-a76b-38c103998297/370829e0-47fb-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywntlz3.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 5 English Explanation 2\">\n\n<p>$$ \\therefore V_{\\text {out }}=V_{I N}+0.7 $$</p>\n\n<p><b>Case 2 :</b> When $0.3 \\mathrm{~V} &lt; V_{I N} &lt; 1.7 \\mathrm{~V}$, both $D_1$ and $D_2$ are OFF. So, the circuit becomes.</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lywnvu2z/dcb209f2-a615-4c17-9d41-f6f48c8f87bd/74e9fdb0-47fb-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnvu30.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lywnvu2z/dcb209f2-a615-4c17-9d41-f6f48c8f87bd/74e9fdb0-47fb-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnvu30.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 5 English Explanation 3\">\n\n<p>$$ \\therefore  V_{\\text {out }}=1 \\mathrm{~V} $$</p>\n\n<p><b>Case 3 :</b> When $V_{I N}&gt;1.7 \\mathrm{~V}, D_1$ is ON and $D_2$ is OFF. So, the circuit becomes,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lywnxxql/3dfd8d75-2eec-4a79-8e14-db0529f3a17c/af5ff6c0-47fb-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnxxrg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lywnxxql/3dfd8d75-2eec-4a79-8e14-db0529f3a17c/af5ff6c0-47fb-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnxxrg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 5 English Explanation 4\">\n\n<p>$V_{\\text {out }}=V_{I N}-0.7$</p>\n\n<p>So, the transfer characteristics can be drawn as shown below,</p>\n\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lywnoi3u/6eb3bf75-63a9-4542-a9af-da384c62693b/a8ffb0a0-47fa-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnoi3v.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lywnoi3u/6eb3bf75-63a9-4542-a9af-da384c62693b/a8ffb0a0-47fa-11ef-a4ec-23a9bd42cec6/file-jaoe38c1lywnoi3v.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2023 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 5 English Explanation 5\">\n\n<p>Hence, the correct option is (A).</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>A circuit and the characteristics of the diode (D) in it are shown. The ratio of the minimum to the maximum small signal voltage gain $${{\\partial {V_{out}}} \\over {\\partial {V_{in}}}}$$ is __________ (rounded off to two decimal places).</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7j6crp1/36546a9c-af84-4f6c-a497-55c1277a3daf/dfd3e650-2a06-11ed-8dda-b7a06b81f81b/file-1l7j6crp2.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7j6crp1/36546a9c-af84-4f6c-a497-55c1277a3daf/dfd3e650-2a06-11ed-8dda-b7a06b81f81b/file-1l7j6crp2.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2022 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 6 English\"></p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "0.75",
    "explanation": "<p>When diode is OFF:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7j6ejia/f47e1156-b58a-45ca-92ef-a8dfa870fdf5/111f1220-2a07-11ed-8dda-b7a06b81f81b/file-1l7j6ejib.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7j6ejia/f47e1156-b58a-45ca-92ef-a8dfa870fdf5/111f1220-2a07-11ed-8dda-b7a06b81f81b/file-1l7j6ejib.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2022 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 6 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>V<sub>o</sub> = 4I</p>\n<p>V<sub>in</sub> = 6I</p>\n<p>A<sub>v</sub> = $${{{V_o}} \\over {{V_{in}}}} = {4 \\over 6} = {2 \\over 3}$$</p>\n<p>When diode is ON, voltage drop across diode is 0.7 V.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l7j6ezq8/5788a31a-13bb-4766-8a0c-ff24d4ce7fab/1da6ed10-2a07-11ed-8dda-b7a06b81f81b/file-1l7j6ezq9.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l7j6ezq8/5788a31a-13bb-4766-8a0c-ff24d4ce7fab/1da6ed10-2a07-11ed-8dda-b7a06b81f81b/file-1l7j6ezq9.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2022 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 6 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$${V_o} = 0.7 + (2\\,k\\Omega )I$$</p>\n<p>$${V_{in}} = 0.7 + (4\\,k\\Omega )I$$</p>\n<p>$$I = {{{V_o} - 0.7} \\over {2k\\Omega }}$$</p>\n<p>$${V_{in}} = 0.7 + (4k\\Omega )\\,.\\,{{({V_o} - 0.7)} \\over {(2k\\Omega )}} = 0.7 + 2{V_o} - 1.4$$</p>\n<p>$${V_o} = {{{V_{in}} + 0.7} \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$$A{'_v} = {{\\partial {V_o}} \\over {\\partial {V_{in}}}} = {1 \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>Maximum voltage gain, $${A_v} = {2 \\over 3}$$</p>\n<p>Minimum voltage gain, $$A{'_v} = {1 \\over 2}$$</p>\n<p>$${{{{(\\partial {V_{out}}/\\partial {V_{in}})}_{\\min }}} \\over {{{(\\partial {V_{out}}/\\partial {V_{in}})}_{\\max }}}} = {{A{'_v}} \\over {{A_v}}} = {1 \\over 2} \\times {3 \\over 2} = {3 \\over 4} = 0.75$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2022,
    "yearKey": "gate-ece-2022",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "content": "The figure shows a half-wave rectifier with a\n475 µF\nfilter capacitor. The load draws a constant\ncurrent I<sub>0</sub>= 1 A from the rectifier. The figure also shows the input voltage V<sub>i</sub>\n, the output\nvoltage V<sub>C</sub> and the peak-to-peak voltage ripple\non V<sub>C</sub>.The input voltage V<sub>i</sub> is a triangle-wave\nwith an amplitude of 10 V and a period of 1 ms.\n<img alt=\"GATE ECE 2016 Set 2 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 7 English 1\" src=\"https://gateclass.cdn.examgoal.net/examside/questions/23f33b30b5b80cc78a132829f06a910d28ca9c817156a8c30043dfcea64a123d.jpg\" style=\"text-align:center;max-width:100%;height:auto;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n<img alt=\"GATE ECE 2016 Set 2 Analog Circuits - Diodes Question 7 English 2\" src=\"https://gateclass.cdn.examgoal.net/examside/questions/a04f5dd685aa45ee690468393721fe8142a9334176fbe0720763802d4a59772e.jpg\" style=\"text-align:center;max-width:100%;height:auto;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n<p>The value of the ripple\nu\n(in volts) is ______________.</p>",
